EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 052300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING A DEEP LOW 969 LIES 200 MILES SW OF
ROCKALL WITH AN ASSOCIATED TROUGH RUNNING FORTH TO
GERMAN BIGHT WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE 989. OVERNIGHT TUESDAY
INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING THE 969 LOW BECOMES CENTRED OVER
SHANNON WHILST THE TROUGH DEEPENS 987 AND MOVS OVER
VIKING. BY MIDDAY THURSDAY THE TROUGH AND THE PARENT LOW
WILL HAVE MERGED AND FILLED WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE 984
OVER SERN SCOTLAND. BY FRIDAY THE LOW WILL HAVE
CONTINUED TO FILL AND IS EXP TO RETREAT NEWARDS INTO
SCANDINAVIA LEAVING A BROAD BUT SLACK TROUGH OVER THE
BRITISH ISLES AND A SECOND SLACK TROUGH DUE S OF MAINLAND
ICELAND. STRG WINDS ARE EXP THROUGH MOST OF THE
PORTPATRICK SHIPPING AREAS TUESDAY EVENING AND THROUGH
WEDNESDAY PERHAPS GALE IN SERN ROCKALL. WINDS GRADUALLY
E ACROSS EERN PORTPATRICK DURING THURSDAY BUT CONTINUING
STRG IN THE W. WINDS MOSTLY EASING TO LIGHT DURING FRIDAY
